div.p:
THE Deity which attended your Cradle, being moſt affectionately fond

of your Glory and Happineſs; doth yet officiouſly purſue the care of your Illuſtrious Perſon, and the Conduct of your Affairs. Often hath ſhe appeared to your Highneſs in broken reflexes, and imperfect ſight, vayled and weakned by your Infant years, but now ſhe repreſents her ſelf to you in her moſt Auguſt and Divine Form and Image, and gives

you her Hand, inviting your Adult Age, to the due exerciſe of your Heroical vertues;
